=head1 DESCRIPTION

The configuration for an Amazon Lex V2 bot.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 InvokedBy => L<Paws::ChimeSDKIdentity::InvokedBy>

Specifies the type of message that triggers a bot.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> LexBotAliasArn => Str

The ARN of the Amazon Lex V2 bot's alias. The ARN uses this format:
C<arn:aws:lex:REGION:ACCOUNT:bot-alias/MYBOTID/MYBOTALIAS>


=head2 B<REQUIRED> LocaleId => Str

Identifies the Amazon Lex V2 bot's language and locale. The string must
match one of the supported locales in Amazon Lex V2. All of the
intents, slot types, and slots used in the bot must have the same
locale. For more information, see Supported languages
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lexv2/latest/dg/how-languages.html) in the
I<Amazon Lex V2 Developer Guide>.


=head2 RespondsTo => Str

B<Deprecated>. Use C<InvokedBy> instead.

Determines whether the Amazon Lex V2 bot responds to all standard
messages. Control messages are not supported.


=head2 WelcomeIntent => Str

The name of the welcome intent configured in the Amazon Lex V2 bot.



